article.description: Tamika Catchings had 16 points and 14 rebounds and Ebony Hoffman added 13 points and a career-high 13 rebounds to help the Fever beat the Shock 67-60 in the season opener for both teams.
article.headline: Saturday night Fever: Indiana tops Shock in opener
article.linkText: Saturday night Fever: Indiana tops Shock in opener
article.story:
INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Tamika Catchings had 16 points and 14 rebounds and Ebony Hoffman added 13 points and a career-high 13 rebounds to help the Indiana Fever beat the Detroit Shock 67-60 on Saturday night in the season opener for both teams.

The Fever used an 11-0 run in the final three minutes to overtake the Shock.

Hoffman made a 19-foot jumper to cut Detroit's lead to 58-56 with 2:45 to play. Forty seconds later, Anna DeForge's 3-pointer gave Indiana the lead for good.

"One of our staples when we came into this year was to pick up our meanness," Hoffman said. "We wanted to be mean again and make people fear us."

Free throws from Catchings, Tamika Whitmore and Tully Bevilaqua helped the Fever build its lead to seven and hold off the Shock, who were picked by the WNBA's general managers to win the Eastern Conference.

"We did everything wrong in the second half," Detroit coach Bill Laimbeer said. "We gave them too many shots, turned the ball over."

Indiana shot 18.8 percent (6-of-32) in the first half and fell behind 29-20. The Fever trailed by as many as 10 points in the second half and struggled to overcome 26 percent shooting.

Katie Smith scored 19 points to lead Detroit, which shot only 37 percent. Cheryl Ford added 10 points and a team-high eight rebounds, and Deanna Nolan scored 10 points.

DeForge, one of three new Indiana starters, scored 14 points, and Whitmore added 13.
